{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"79fabf92-51c9-40eb-b9ef-63a8a8b33643","content":"Here are the **evaluation performance issues** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. File I/O Property Function (High Impact)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nReading files during evaluation is expensive — it blocks the evaluation pipeline with synchronous disk I/O. This runs on every evaluation (IDE refreshes, builds, restores). **Fix:** Move file reading to a target at execution time instead.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Expensive Glob Pattern (Medium Impact)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThe `**\\*.*` glob walks the entire directory tree during evaluation. If the tree is large (e.g., contains `node_modules`, `.git`, or large artifact directories), this becomes very costly. **Fix:** Use `DefaultItemExcludes` to pre-exclude heavy directories, or narrow the glob to specific subdirectories/extensions.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deep Import Chain (Low-Medium Impact)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nThree levels of chained imports. While shallow here, this pattern scales poorly. Each import adds evaluation overhead. Deep chains (>20 levels) significantly slow evaluation. Keep import depth minimal and flatten where possible.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Issue | Severity | Fix |\n|-------|----------|-----|\n| `File::ReadAllText` in property | 🔴 High | Move to execution-time target |\n| `**\\*.*` glob | 🟡 Medium | Narrow pattern or add exclusions |\n| Chained imports (3 deep) | 🟢 Low | Acceptable, but watch for growth |\n\nThe file I/O property function is the most impactful issue — it defeats caching and penalizes every evaluation pass.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7cb0f1e7-ce43-4bda-985a-300aa1d31ebe","outputTokens":457,"requestId":"EC11:2EA4C2:814067:A08D6E:6A0130FA"},"id":"6a9d065e-0d93-417a-a205-53dfb6284579","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:29:41.387Z","parentId":"3c32606e-f394-4447-9890-69c207c79863"}
